The number of international schools has doubled over the past decade, from about 5,000 to more than 10,200 this year, according to International Schools Consultancy, a company that provides data on the schools.
"These schools are resource-rich," said Rajiv Bhat, chief operating officer of Search Associates, a recruitment company for international schools.
For American educators accustomed to working in low-income schools, the resources available at some international schools can seem luxurious.
Elsewhere in the school that afternoon, high school students were working on advanced math and kindergartners were painting in a glass-walled atelier.
Housing benefits help save moneyInternational school teachers sometimes earn less than what they earned in the States.